{"id":"project-LICHEN-auq9","title":"coap_config.c: sync_word hex parsing can overflow","description":"File: lichen/subsys/lichen/coap/coap_config.c
Lines: 421-436

The sync_word hex string parser has no length validation:
```c
unsigned long v = 0;
for (size_t i = 2; i < val.len; i++) {
    char c = (char)val.value[i];
    v <<= 4;
    ...
}
```

If the CBOR payload contains a very long hex string (e.g., '0x' followed by 100 hex chars), this will:
1. Overflow 'v' (unsigned long) causing undefined behavior on shift
2. Only the final 64/32 bits are retained, then truncated to uint16_t

Should validate val.len <= 6 (for '0x' + up to 4 hex digits for uint16_t).

